The paper deals with the dimensions of BCH codes, which are widely used in communication and data storage systems. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of minimum distances of primitive BCH codes, which can be categorized under discrete structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The investigation of dimensions of codes can also be considered as a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the exploration of BCH codes over finite fields, which can be related to the topic of signal processing (cs.SI).
